(
  'Lookalike & High-Value Prospect Expansion',
  'Prospecting & Awareness',
  'When I need to grow my customer base efficiently, I want to find and target new audiences that behave like my best customers so I can reduce acquisition costs and scale revenue from high-value segments',
  'Ads, Display, Social, CRM',
  'Insight, Listener, Connection, Segmentation, AIWB',
  'Incremental Revenue Lift (revenue lift per $ of spend, driven by BlueConic optimized segments) - Definition: additional revenue generated per $ of spend when BlueConic-orchestrated lookalike segments/audiences are used, compared to: 1. the same spend through native platform lookalikes or 2. the brand''s historical acquisition baseline',
  'Lookalike performance lift (i.e CTR, CAC, ROAS, CPA, AOV etc.)',
  'There are no pre-trained lookalike models available, so the customer will either need to bring their own model (BYOM) or have AI Workbench (AIWB) notebooks developed to train new models. This requires a thorough discovery phase to define hypotheses, features, conversion events, targeting rules, control group size, and other key parameters. Once development begins, the model must be trained and allowed to converge before it can deliver optimal results - a process that may take time and impact overall timelines. There is also the maintenance aspect to this - who is responsible for providing support and maintaining these customer-trained models?',
  'Develop templatized solutions for the most common "Next Best" models (action/offer/channel). By defining a standardized framework we can significantly reduce the amount of time spent on the discovery phase. In practice, this means teams can quickly configure, train and deploy predictive models, rather than starting from scratch each time. This approach improves efficiency, accelerates time to value, and ensures greater consistency and quality across implementations.',
  'Templatized AIWB notebooks for training lookalike, audience selection, next best channel selection models. Predefined feature sets (e.g., recency, frequency, average order value, engagement metrics, channel affinity) and hypothesis scaffolds that teams can customize. Standardized output segments, e.g. "high-value lookalike prospects". Standardized customer data schema and Listeners setup designed for acquisition and lookalike use cases - including key attributes like: purchase history, engagement frequency, conversion events, channel touchpoints. Purpose-built Connections to common ecommerce platforms (Shopify, Magento, Salesforce Commerce Cloud) for transactional syncs. OOTB Dashboards for tracking ROAS, CAC, and conversion lift vs. platform-based lookalikes, etc.',
  'Data readiness - First-party behavioral and transactional data. Feature/hypothesis alignment for lookalike modeling. Minimum volume of known customers (e.g., 5K–10K active buyers) to train a meaningful lookalike model. Access to advertising platforms where modeled audiences can be activated. Clear understanding of business objective, success metrics',
  'Discovery: 2 wks, Implementation: 4 wks (AIWB notebook to train lookalike models), Go-Live: 1 wk, Total: ~7 wks. Future: OOTB AIWB notebook to train Lookalike models + standardized data schema can potentially reduce TTV to <4 wks',
  true
),
(
  'Intent-Based Media Targeting',
  'Prospecting & Awareness',
  'When I invest in paid media, I want to identify and prioritize audiences that show genuine intent so I can optimize spend toward buyers who are most likely to convert.',
  'Social, Ads, Display, CTV, Paid Search, DSP',
  'Connection, Segmentation, Listener, AIWB',
  'Incremental Media Efficiency: The incremental conversions or revenue per paid media impression, driven by BlueConic''s intent activation vs alternatives. Definition: % improvement in conversion or revenue yield per media impression or $ achieved when BlueConic''s intent signals are used to drive media activation or suppression, compared to 1) the same campaign without BlueConic intent data or 2) the brand''s historical baseline for targeting',
  'CPM, CPA, CPL, CPC, ROAS',
  'No pre-trained NBA models available for predicting intention.',
  'Templatized solutions that include pre-defined CDP Listener setups and example segment definitions, intent prediction model. Internal team or agency resource dedicated to building and testing Experiences.',
  'Templatized solutions that include Experience templates, pre-defined CDP Listener setups and example segment definitions, NBA model. Internal team or agency resource dedicated to building and testing Experiences.',
  'Data readiness - consistent website tagging to support capturing intent. Feature/hypotheses alignment for NBA model. Experience ownership: access to front-end / design support for styling and layout. Clear understanding of business objective, success metrics. Access to advertising platforms where intent-based audiences can be activated',
  'Discovery: 2 wks, Implementation: 4 wks (AIWB notebook to train intent prediction model), Go-Live: 1 wk, Total: ~7 wks. Future: OOTB AIWB notebook to train intent prediction models + standardized data schema can potentially reduce TTV to <4 wks',
  true
),
(
