  'Incremental Identity Conversion Rate: % increase in new, consented, first party identities created when BlueConic''s features are used, compared to the brand''s historical/baseline rate.',
  'Known-to-anonymous ratio, Profile Merge rate, Consent Capture Rate',
  'The number and type of Experiences (XPs) is the primary risk factor: our standard onboarding model for Experiences is "self-onboarding with guidance", meaning that we provide training but the customer team is responsible for building, configuring, and launching the Experiences themselves. While this model promotes customer independence and scalability, it introduces variability in time-to-launch and overall impact depending on the complexity of the Experiences (simple quiz vs outcome-based vs DPF). Depending on the type/complexity of the Experience, it can take up to 45 days for a customer to launch their first Experience.',
  'Templatized solutions that include Experience templates, pre-defined CDP Listener setups. Internal team or agency resource dedicated to building and testing Experiences.',
  'Pre-configured, click-to-clone templates for common Experience types (quiz, survey, product matcher, lead capture). Predefined Listeners and CDP/XP connection for capturing intent and first-party data.',
  'Data readiness - consistent website tagging to support capturing intent/behaviour/interest. Experience ownership: access to front-end / design support for customizing styling and layout. Clear understanding of business objective, success metrics.',
  'Discovery: 1 wks, Implementation: 4 wks (2 Experiences, customer-built), Go-Live: 1 wk, Total: ~6 wks. Future: AI Experience Builder can potentially reduce Implementation time, no data available yet to estimate impact',
  true
),
